enhanced_by.reason: Both methods involve operations on the composite maps, making it beneficial to reuse setup involving map composition.
Initializing the composite map with specific maps can be reused to set up the state for testing containsValue.
The put method adds key-value pairs to the composite maps, which can affect the result of containsValue.
The remove method can remove key-value pairs from the composite maps, which can affect the result of containsValue.
